the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Theresa, your role in this game is seer.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nAt Night 1, You have checked Elaine, the result is: werewolf.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nAllison's speech: Good morning, everyone. As we begin our first day, it's important to remember that our goal is to identify and eliminate the werewolves. I want to emphasize the importance of working together and considering multiple perspectives as we make our decisions. While it's natural to feel anxious and suspicious, we must remain calm and rational in our analysis. I haven't noticed any overtly suspicious behavior from any of the players, but I encourage everyone to share their observations and concerns. Let's focus on protecting key players like the Seer, Guard, and Witch, if they are identified, and work together to ensure the village's survival.\nCharlene's speech: Thank you, Allison, for your insightful words. It's crucial that we work together and remain calm and rational as we navigate this challenge. I would like to introduce myself as the Guard. My role is to protect key players each night, and I believe this is essential for our survival. Last night, I protected Pamela, and I will continue to do so as long as I am able. It's important that we identify and protect the Seer and Witch, as they are vital to our efforts. Let's all share our observations and work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. We can do this if we stay united and focused.\nElaine's speech: Thank you, Allison and Charlene, for your insightful words. I would like to introduce myself as the Seer. Last night, I checked a player's identity, and I can confirm that they are not a werewolf. I believe it's crucial that we stay united and focused on our goal of eliminating the werewolves. I have also protected someone last night, but I will not reveal who it was to avoid raising suspicion. Let's all share our observations and work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. We can do this if we stay united and focused.\nFrank's speech: Thank you, Allison, Charlene, and Elaine, for your insightful words. It's clear that we need to stay united and focused on our goal of eliminating the werewolves. I fully agree with Allison's emphasis on unity and rationality. Charlene, your role as the Guard is crucial for our survival, and I have no reason to doubt your commitment to protecting key players. Elaine, your role as the Seer is also vital, and I trust your judgment in identifying werewolves. Last night, I took actions to protect key players, just as you both did. Let's all share our observations and work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. We can do this if we stay united and focused.\nGary's speech: Thank you, Allison, Charlene, Elaine, and Frank, for your insightful words. It's clear that we need to stay united and focused on our goal of eliminating the werewolves. I fully agree with Allison's emphasis on unity and rationality. Charlene, your role as the Guard is crucial for our survival, and I have no reason to doubt your commitment to protecting key players. Elaine, your role as the Seer is also vital, and I trust your judgment in identifying werewolves. Frank, your support for both of them adds to their credibility. However, I believe it's important that we all share our observations and concerns. I have also taken actions to protect key players,